# FastAPI backend rules

Read `.ai/stack-backend-fastapi.md` for full detail.

- Layering: routers → services → repositories. Routers stay thin (HTTP only), never touch the DB.
- Never return SQLAlchemy models from endpoints — map to Pydantic response schemas.
- Async endpoints and async DB sessions; don't block the event loop.
- Validate all input with Pydantic v2; raise typed domain errors mapped to HTTP handlers.
- Config/secrets via Pydantic Settings from env — never hard-coded.
- All schema changes through Alembic, backward-compatible.
- Tests: pytest; unit-test services without a DB, integration-test routers with httpx.
- Lint/format with ruff, types with mypy (strict) — must pass before commit.

